Networking Services: VPC, Subnets, and Load Balancing

ğŸ§  Networking Services Overview
ğŸŒ 1. Virtual Private Cloud (VPC)
A VPC is a logically isolated network in the cloud where you can launch cloud resources (e.g., servers, databases). It gives full control over IP ranges, subnets, route tables, and gateways.

ğŸ§± 2. Subnets
Subnets divide a VPC into smaller network segments.

Public Subnet: Exposed to the internet (e.g., web servers)

Private Subnet: Internal communication only (e.g., databases)

ğŸ›£ï¸ 3. Custom Route Tables
Route tables direct traffic between subnets, internet gateways, and NAT. You can define custom paths for specific subnets.

ğŸ” 4. Security Groups
Security groups act like virtual firewalls controlling inbound and outbound traffic to ECS instances (virtual servers) based on rules.

âš–ï¸ 5. Load Balancer (ELB)
An Elastic Load Balancer (ELB) automatically distributes incoming traffic across multiple backend servers, improving availability and scalability.


